document_data.Geography:
Halfhap was located on the [[Moonsea Ride]] at the edge of the [[Stonelands]], halfway between the [[Thunder Peaks]] and the [[Storm Horns]]. [[Tilverton]] was about {{SI|60|mile|k|long=yes}} to the northeast, the closest major settlement.{{Cite interactive atlas|Sembia}} To the southwest, the Ride climbed through [[Gnoll Pass]] and beyond the [[Storm Horns]], reaching [[Castle Crag]] and then [[Arabel]] at the terminus of the Moonsea Ride about {{SI|130|mile|k|long=yes}} away. 

The [[Stonebolt Trail]] bypassed Halfhap and Tilverton entirely, running in a straight line across the Stonelands from Gnoll Pass to [[Shadow Gap]].{{Cite interactive atlas|Cormyr}}

Other notable sites in the area included the ruins of [[Darkenshield]], the [[Tower of Ruin]], and [[Wyvernwatch Castle]].
